passages.text: Japan | Transport & Logistics
Japan Airport Terminal
Equity Research August 30, 2025

JAT issued corporate bonds on August 28th to refinance its hybrid loan. We think this is positive as the hybrid loan was the bottleneck for reassessing its shareholder return policy, in our view, and we foresee a favorable set- up for a renewed capital allocation strategy with a buyback program in the next MTP.

Impression: Positive. JAT issued ¥20bn of corporate bonds (¥5bn 5-year, ¥15bn 10-year tenure) on August 28th to refinance its hybrid loan. JAT had previously announced its plan to refinance the loan at Q1 results announcement on August 6th, and we think this is positive as the hybrid loan was the bottleneck for reassessing its shareholder return policy, in our view, with large % of JAT's outstanding shares owned by other corporates leading to valuation discounts from possible sell- down. Thus, we foresee a favorable set- up for a renewed capital allocation strategy with a buyback program in the next MTP due to be announced in May 2026.
Earnings forecasts and valuation: We update our estimates and forecast OP of ¥41.7bn (+8.3% YoY) for FY3/26 and ¥44.9bn in FY27. Maintain Buy and PT ¥6,700.

1. We believe steady growth in the inbound tourist market is possible thanks to the structural growth in global income.  
2. If duty-free shopping of inbound tourists surges thanks to ¥ depreciation, there could be significant profit upside.
Risk/Reward - 12 Month View

1. Organic growth rate of passengers on domestic routes to/from Haneda at +0.3% CAGR over 2024-2034, with growth in leisure travel vs decline in business travel due to increasing prevalence of online meetings.  
2. Organic growth rate of passengers on international routes to/from Haneda at +4.8% CAGR over 2024-2034, with structural growth in inbound tourism.  
3. Duty-free shopping ASP continues to increase thanks to volume gains and yen weakness.  
4. Price target of ¥6,700 equates to an FY3/26E EV/EBITDA of 10.5x.

1. Domestic business travel is not disrupted by the rise in online meetings.  
2. Inbound tourist numbers grow and recover faster than our expectations.  
3. Improvement in shareholders' return.  
4. Shopping volume accelerates significantly.  
5. Upside price target of ¥7,900 equates to FY3/26E EV/EBITDA of 12.1x.

1. Domestic business travel is disrupted by the rise in online meetings more significantly than we expect.  
2. Shopping by inbound travelers slows due to the emergence of alternatives or changes in forex.  
3. Equity finance.  
4. Downside price target of ¥3,900 equates to FY3/25E EV/EBITDA of 6.9x.

We believe Merchandise Quality & Safety is the most important issue. As the owner and operator of airport facilities that are major parts of transportation infrastructure, quality and safety are required to protect a large number of domestic and international passengers. Energy Management is also important. As a large airport facility, efforts to save energy are efficient both for profit and for the environment.
